<TITLE> CU forms probe committee over BCL death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Apr 17 (bdnews24.com) -- The Chittagong University has formed a four-member probe committee following the death of a student. The committee headed by Mohammad Al Amin, a professor of forestry and environmental science, has been asked to submit its findings within 15 days, university proctor Jashim Uddin told bdnews24.com. The decision came in an emergency syndicate meeting on Saturday. Md Asaduzzaman, an activist of the Chhatra League's university unit, was killed on Apr 17 in a clash with locals. He was a student of accounting and information. BCL called an indefinite strike in the campus and the university authorities postponed all classes and exams for three days. bdnews24.c
